Blaze.uk.description: Extraterrestrial Devices: Experts discuss the technological capabilities of ancient civilizations and how this device challenges the understanding of their knowledge. (S1, ep 9)

Blaze.uk.description: Real Excalibur & Texas Teleportation: A sword discovered at the bottom of a river may be the famed Excalibur. Also, a doorbell cam captures possible proof of teleportation. (S2, ep 4)

Blaze.uk.title: The Proof Is Out There
Blaze.uk.description: Malaysian Toilet Monster & The Buzzer: A large black creature emerging from a family's toilet could be some kind of mythical creature. An astronaut spots something intriguing. (S2, ep 5)

Blaze.uk.title: The Proof Is Out There
Blaze.uk.description: Solar Spaceship and Invisibility Cloak: Could a breed of dogs have the power to freeze time? Do invisibility cloaks really exist? The team examine the videos and reach a verdict. (S2, ep 6)

Blaze.uk.title: The Proof Is Out There
Blaze.uk.description: Two-Headed Serpent and Mummified Monster: A mysterious creature is discovered in Russia, a possible genetic experiment goes wrong and a fire has a mind of its own. (S2, ep 7)

Blaze.uk.title: Cursed Treasures
Blaze.uk.description: From the time of the Knights Templar to pre-historic Spain, uncover the origins of the curses surrounding the Turin Shroud, the Cave of Altamira and more.

Blaze.uk.title: Cursed Treasures
Blaze.uk.description: From India at the time of the Mughal Empire to the Assyrian city of Nineveh, uncover the origins of the curses surrounding the Koh-i-Noor, the Neo-Assyrian Stele and more. (S1, ep 6)

Blaze.uk.title: Forbidden History
Blaze.uk.description: The Quest to Find the Tomb of Mary Magdalene: Experts look to uncover the truth behind the mystery of Mary Magdalene's life after witnessing the resurrection. (S7, ep 3)

Blaze.uk.title: Forbidden History
Blaze.uk.description: The Mysteries of the World's Oldest Temple: The rock-hewn pillars of Gobekli Tepe in Turkey have baffled archaeologists for decades - who built this incredible monument, and why? (S7, ep 4)

Blaze.uk.title: New: Empire Builders
Blaze.uk.description: Mexico (Part 1): Delve into the often-overlooked history of America's next-door neighbour to explore the epic, violent and bloody struggles of Mexican culture and identity. (S2, ep 11)

Blaze.uk.title: New: Empire Builders
Blaze.uk.description: Mexico (Part 2): Explore further a chronicle of conquest with bloody and dramatic consequences littered throughout Mexican history. (S2, ep 12)

Blaze.uk.title: Secrets In The Sky: Untold Story
Blaze.uk.description: ...Skunk Works. For the first time in 75 years, the secretive aerospace division opens its hangar doors to reveal more about the cloak-and-dagger world of their Skunk Works programme.

Blaze.uk.title: Mysteries From Above
Blaze.uk.description: Perplexing Patterns: Explore a psychedelic swirl in the Utah wastelands, a bizarre configuration of circles in the Sahara and a remote polka-dot lake in Canada. (S3, ep 7)

E4Plus1.uk.description: The Bon Voyage Reaction: Leonard is offered an exciting job opportunity that will keep him out of the country for several months. Raj pushes the boundaries of his relationship. (S6 Ep24)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Hofstadter Insufficiency: Sheldon and Penny bond while Leonard is away. Raj finds someone to share his heartache. Bernadette and Amy attract male attention at a conference. (S7 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Faith Off: Homer gets a bucket of superglue stuck to his head and the only person who can remove it is a preacher (Don Cheadle), who inspires Bart to become a faith healer. (S11 Ep11/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Mansion Family: Mr Burns leaves town for a full medical check-up, leaving the Simpsons in charge of his mansion. Guest starring Britney Spears as herself. (S11 Ep12/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Saddlesore Galactica: Homer and Bart save a horse from the fair and decide to train him as an American footballer. Or maybe a racehorse. (S11 Ep13/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox Festive Special
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Goggleboxers check out top Christmas telly, from The Real Full Monty: Jingle Bells to An Audience with Kylie, The 1% Club Christmas Special, Fur Babies, Men Up and Love Actually.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Celebrity Traitors is on this time. There's Game of Wool: Britain's Best Knitter. And Trigger Point, Hunted, Squid Game: The Challenge and Hamza's Hidden Wild Isles. (S26 Ep10) [SL]

Film4.uk.title: Wrath of Man
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Jason Statham reunites with director Guy Ritchie to give it both barrels as a mysterious hardman working for a money truck firm that keeps getting hit. But is he an inside man?

Film4.uk.title: The Mechanic
Film4.uk.description: (2011) Thriller with Jason Statham and Donald Sutherland. A hitman is ordered to kill his mentor, but then takes on the dead man's son as an apprentice. Could get complicated... and deadly.

Film4.uk.title: Carol
Film4.uk.description: (2015) Drama based on Patricia Highsmith's ground-breaking novel. A wealthy married woman (Cate Blanchett) falls in love with a younger woman (Rooney Mara) who works in a department store.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Cover Girl
Film4.uk.description: (1944) Rita Hayworth and Gene Kelly star in Charles Vidor's Technicolor comedy musical about a chorus girl's rise to fame. Featuring songs and a score from Jerome Kern and Ira Gershwin.

Film4.uk.title: Dead of Night
Film4.uk.description: (1945) Five uncanny tales of the supernatural in one eerie package, the most famous starring ventriloquist Michael Redgrave and a deadly dummy. Prepare to be spooked.

Film4.uk.title: Anastasia
Film4.uk.description: (1956) Historical drama. The Oscar-winning Ingrid Bergman stars as an amnesiac refugee who Yul Brynner tries to pass off as the daughter of the murdered Tsar of Russia, Nicholas II.

Film4.uk.title: Dr Who and the Daleks
Film4.uk.description: (1965) A spin-off of the cult television series starring Peter Cushing. Backyard-inventor Dr Who finds himself stuck on the irradiated planet Skaro, home of the cold and metallic Daleks.

Film4.uk.title: Rosaline
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Literary romcom with Kaitlyn Dever and Isabela Merced. This is the story of Juliet's cousin who gets dumped by Romeo at the start of Shakespeare's play... and she's not too pleased.

Film4.uk.title: Mrs Harris Goes to Paris
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Lesley Manville stars as a cleaner who saves up and heads to Paris to get herself a Dior couture dress, in director Anthony Fabian's fabulous, Oscar-nominated period comedy drama.

Film4.uk.title: American Gangster
Film4.uk.description: (2007) True crime thriller directed by Ridley Scott. An outcast New York cop (Russell Crowe) is charged with bringing down entrepreneurial Harlem drug lord Frank Lucas (Denzel Washington).

Film4.uk.title: Thief
Film4.uk.description: (1971) Crime thriller starring Richard Crenna. A recently paroled thief must do one last job to pay off old debts. But can he get away with it and build a life with his new girlfriend?

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Henry VIII and His Six Wives
Film4.uk.description: (1972) Historical drama with Keith Michell as Henry VIII, nobly supported by Donald Pleasance, Charlotte Rampling and Jane Asher. The dying monarch reviews his own life.

Film4.uk.title: The Desert Fox
Film4.uk.description: (1951) Drama. James Mason stars in Henry Hathaway's sympathetic portrait of Field Marshal Erwin Rommel in the final years of his life during the Second World War. With Jessica Tandy.

Film4.uk.title: The Lavender Hill Mob
Film4.uk.description: (1951) Classic Ealing comedy starring Alec Guinness as a mild-mannered bank clerk who assembles a gang to hijack a million quid's worth of gold. Which is when their problems really start...

Film4.uk.title: Daleks Invasion Earth 2150 A.D.
Film4.uk.description: (1966) A sci-fi classic with Peter Cushing. Dr Who travels to the future only to find the Daleks have conquered the Earth! Can he stop them nuking the planet's core? With Bernard Cribbins.

Film4.uk.title: Oblivion
Film4.uk.description: (2013) Sci-fi action-mystery set on a war-ravaged planet Earth that's been largely abandoned by humanity. With Tom Cruise, Andrea Riseborough, Olga Kurylenko and Morgan Freeman.

Film4.uk.title: Good Luck to You, Leo Grande
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Drama starring Emma Thompson as a recently widowed, retired teacher who has a sexual bucket list she wants to get around to now that she has the time and, perhaps, even the energy.

Film4.uk.title: Mission: Impossible - Fallout
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Tom Cruise stars in part six of the action-thriller series. His mission: to stop terrorists from getting their hands on nuclear bombs and unleashing global devastation.

Film4.uk.title: The Outsiders
Film4.uk.description: (1983) Francis Ford Coppola's seminal brat pack coming-of-age crime drama with Tom Cruise, Patrick Swayze, Ralph Macchio, Matt Dillon and Rob Lowe. Two teenage tribes go to war in Tulsa.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Jingle All the Way
Film4.uk.description: (1996) Brian Levant's festive all-action comedy. Arnold Schwarzenegger is on a mission to get his son (Jake Lloyd) the must-have Christmas toy, Turbo Man. But it's sold out everywhere...

Film4.uk.title: Hue & Cry
Film4.uk.description: (1947) The very first Ealing comedy is set in the post-war East End. A boy tries to catch a gang of thieves who are using his favourite comic to communicate their dastardly deeds.

Film4.uk.title: Mysterious Island
Film4.uk.description: (1961) Sci-fi adventure based on Jules Verne's novel. Two men fleeing the US Civil War find an island inhabited by monsters (animated by Ray Harryhausen) and the mysterious Captain Nemo.

Film4.uk.title: Mr Popper's Penguins
Film4.uk.description: (2011) Family comedy. Jim Carrey stars as a work-obsessed New York property developer whose life is turned upside down when he receives a crate containing six live penguins.

Film4.uk.title: Midway
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Roland Emmerich's sprawling, action-packed war drama about the Battle of Midway, a major turning point in World War II. Starring Ed Skrein, Luke Evans and Woody Harrelson.

Film4.uk.title: The Menu
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Horror with Ralph Fiennes and Anya Taylor-Joy. Only one diner at an exclusive eatery sees through the foam quenelles to the pile of steaming prairie oysters beyond. Mayhem ensues.

Film4.uk.title: Nightmare Alley
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Guillermo del Toro's star-studded carny thriller with Bradley Cooper and Cate Blanchett. Can a chancer with a dark past use clairvoyancy to fleece rich New Yorkers out of a fortune?
